{
  "page": "Cymmeri",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Cymmeri</b> were an ancient people of the grasslands of central <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a>, who established their kingdoms among the hills. They were at some point conquered and assimilated by the <a href=\"/index.php/Tall_Men\" title=\"Tall Men\">Tall Men</a>. According to legend, the daughter of their greatest ruler was married by <a href=\"/index.php/Huzhor_Amai\" title=\"Huzhor Amai\">Huzhor Amai</a>, bringing the Cymmeri under his rule. The Cymmeri wife of Amai was charged with making his armor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Grasslands_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Grasslands-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Cymmeri are the first people known to have worked iron.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Grasslands_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Grasslands-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cymmeri&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Cymmeri may be inspired by the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cimmerians\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Cimmerians\">Cimmerians</a>, a nomadic Indo-European people who appear in Assyrian and Greco-Roman records. In particular, they may be a reference to the fictionalized Cimmerians which appear in the <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conan_the_Barbarian\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Conan the Barbarian\">Conan the Barbarian</a></i> stories by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_E._Howard\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Robert E. Howard\">Robert E. Howard</a>. Conan's stories were among <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>'s youth reads.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cymmeri&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Grasslands-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Grasslands_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Grasslands_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>The World of ice and Fire</i>, The Grasslands</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/Not_a_Blog\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Not a Blog\">Not a Blog</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://georgerrmartin.com/notablog/2013/03/13/reading-recommendations/\">Reading Recommendations</a> (March 13, 2013)</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0;;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:2px;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;width:100%;color:inherit;;;\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" style=\";\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist\" style=\"display:block;float:left;font-weight:normal;font-size:88%;padding-top:3px;text-align:left;width:6.8em;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/index.php/Template:Cultures\" title=\"Template:Cultures\"><span title=\"View this template\" style=\";;background:none transparent;border:none;\">v</span